1928;;The Law of the Range;;American;;William Nigh;;Tim McCoy, Joan Crawford, Rex Lease;;western;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Law_of_the_Range;;Betty Dallas (Crawford) is a passenger on a stagecoach that is held up by an outlaw named The Solitaire Kid (Lease). Ranger Jim Lockhart (McCoy), who is Betty's sweetheart, is in pursuit of The Solitaire Kid, and in the end, as the two men face one another, there is a mortal shoot-out.